      <div class="ya-framing reveal" data-section="thesis">
        <p class="quote">A Series C buys reach. The risk is spending it on more features for the metro flyer Scapia already won. <span class="grad">The growth is somewhere else: the next ten million, who travel for faith first and fly for the first time.</span></p>
        <p class="tail">Two traps follow a raise built on "more offerings": <strong>feature sprawl</strong> and rising <strong>acquisition cost</strong> as the easy metro base runs dry. Anil Goteti framed the goal as "products that help our users travel and lead richer lives." The three stops below sequence exactly that, for the customer the funding is actually chasing.</p>
