            <h3 class="stop-title">Start where India already travels</h3>
            <div class="stop-sub">The biggest first journey is not a holiday. It is a pilgrimage.</div>
            <div class="stop-divider"></div>
            <div class="ya-row">
              <span class="ya-row-ic gap" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg></span>
              <div class="ya-row-body">
                <div class="ya-row-label gap">The gap</div>
                <p>Zero forex markup and international lounges speak to the <em>metro outbound flyer</em>. But the 7x growth and the next ten million sit in Tier 2 and Tier 3, where the highest-intent, group-sized, repeat travel is faith: <strong>Tirupati, Vaishno Devi, the Char Dham, Shirdi, Ajmer, the Kumbh</strong>. No premium travel-fintech is built for it.</p>
